issue.title: Powershell - extra characters are added unexpectedly
issue.body:

Platform: Windows x64 10.0.19045
Plugins: none
Frontend: xterm-webgl

When moving the cursor right-to-left over existing text, `[D` sequences are inserted sporadically:
![image](https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby/assets/14366592/4d439fce-3e94-4aad-80b1-d1d052efdd33)

issue.title: PowerShell automatically adding current directory to function parameters during function calls
issue.body:
<!--
# READ CAREFULLY:

* **ENGLISH ONLY** - this issue tracker is English-only. Please respect the people who take time to help you with your problems.
* Search existing issues first: https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby/issues
* Test with the latest Tabby version: https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby/releases
* Disable third-party plugins.
-->

**Describe the problem**:
When using the PowerShell terminal, it auto completes the current directory shortcut (.\\) on every Shift+{key} stroke during a function call.

**To Reproduce**:
Pretend you have a powershell command named `myfn` that takes 1 string parameter. 
1. Open the PowerShell terminal 
2. Type `myfn` and press space
3. Pressing `shift` `"` will trigger the (.\\) before your string

This is not desired because the fn only wants a string, not a path character and thus will error out. This will happen with any shift+{key} stroke during a function call.

Cannot figure out how to turn this off.

comment.body:
I was about to raise this separately, but I think it's related.

I get the same behavior, but also noticed it when doing `Shift` + `u` in which case I get the following: 
![image](https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby/assets/14366592/d281117e-ce96-44ce-b30c-a1c793a4537f)

If however I do `Shift` + `d` (where there are files starting with "d" in the current directory) I get this:
![image](https://github.com/Eugeny/tabby/assets/14366592/d26fc2ad-111a-4cdd-9c44-6ee70590ca19)

I too am unable to find how to change or disable this. It doesn't appear to be configurable through shortcuts, or enabled by any of the plugins

issue.title: The ability to disable the fading of text on unfocused terminals
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I find it very distracting that Tabby fades out the text in unfocused terminals. I would like to see an option to disable the fading. I already know which terminal is the active one based on how the cursor looks, this fading is unnecessary for me. Often times I need to be reading the text in the unfocused terminals and this makes it much harder on the eyes.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
As an alternative you could add a thin border around the active terminal as an option instead, and also allow no fading and no border for those of us who would prefer that.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Not applicable.

**Additional context**
No additonal context to add at this time.
